layers which is pretty cool.

13
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:34,710
Here, let me undo that.

14
00:00:34,710 --> 00:00:37,630
Being able to control separate
parts of this image individually

15
00:00:37,630 --> 00:00:40,680
makes it much easier to put
together something complex.

16
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:42,080
Photoshop uses layers too,

17
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:45,990
as does pretty much every other piece
of visual media creation software.

18
00:00:45,990 --> 00:00:47,780
Our video production team, for example,

19
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:52,740
uses Adobe Premier to composite all
the videos that you watch on Udacity.

20
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:56,510
In fact, these tablet style
videos have two main layers.

21
00:00:56,510 --> 00:01:00,020
We create one layer by doing
a screen recording on the tablet.

22
00:01:00,020 --> 00:01:03,610
And then we create a second layer with
a camera above the tablet pointed

23
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:05,140
down at our hands.

24
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:09,060
When the two are composited it together,
we put the tablet on top of the hand so

25
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:12,960
that no matter where the hand is on the
screen, you can always read the text.

26
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,338
Pretty cool?

